1
00:01:25,690 --> 00:01:35,000
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:37,930
[Episode 21]

3
00:01:39,539 --> 00:01:39,979
Hello.

4
00:01:40,650 --> 00:01:41,200
Hello.

5
00:01:41,280 --> 00:01:41,680
Hello.

6
00:01:41,850 --> 00:01:42,539
I've also been

7
00:01:42,539 --> 00:01:44,979
selling goods in the market lately.

8
00:01:45,539 --> 00:01:46,289
I'm a vendor like you

9
00:01:46,289 --> 00:01:47,570
and a fellow countryman.

10
00:01:47,570 --> 00:01:48,210
We're all Chinese.

11
00:01:48,210 --> 00:01:49,039
Nice to meet you.

12
00:01:49,039 --> 00:01:49,840
My surname is Du.

13
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:51,100
You can just call me Du.

14
00:01:52,210 --> 00:01:53,210
How may I help you?

15
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:56,580
I meant to say hello to you guys

16
00:01:57,140 --> 00:01:58,600
on the day of your arrival.

17
00:01:58,950 --> 00:02:01,100
But your stall was too popular.

18
00:02:01,340 --> 00:02:03,180
I didn't even manage to squeeze in.

19
00:02:03,180 --> 00:02:04,640
How kind of you to say that.

20
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:05,780
It's pretty cold out here.

21
00:02:05,780 --> 00:02:06,730
Would you like to talk inside?

22
00:02:06,730 --> 00:02:08,330
No, no. I'm not going inside.

23
00:02:08,630 --> 00:02:09,300
See,

24
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:11,610
you guys have been here for a while.

25
00:02:11,690 --> 00:02:12,410
Well,

26
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:14,000
there's a nice Chinese restaurant

27
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:14,630
nearby.

28
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:16,840
How about we have a gathering there?

29
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:18,060
We are all Chinese, aren't we?

30
00:02:18,060 --> 00:02:19,460
We can eat and talk there.

31
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:19,960
Hello.

32
00:02:20,190 --> 00:02:20,650
Sir.

33
00:02:20,860 --> 00:02:21,790
What's going on?

34
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:24,740
This is Mr. Du,
a fellow vendor in the market.

35
00:02:25,090 --> 00:02:25,970
Just call me Du.

36
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,890
He's inviting us to dinner.

37
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:30,280
There is no time like the present.

38
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:31,140
Shall we go now?

39
00:02:33,460 --> 00:02:34,210
Mr. Du.

40
00:02:35,190 --> 00:02:35,500
Jun.

41
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:36,630
Why talk by the door?

42
00:02:36,930 --> 00:02:37,810
You know each other?

43
00:02:37,810 --> 00:02:38,400
Yes.

44
00:02:39,860 --> 00:02:40,310
Mr. Du

45
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:41,579
is quite famous in our circle

46
00:02:41,579 --> 00:02:42,740
of resellers.

47
00:02:43,770 --> 00:02:45,340
Jun's here too, huh?

48
00:02:45,340 --> 00:02:45,860
Everyone is here.

49
00:02:45,860 --> 00:02:46,530
Let's go eat.

50
00:02:46,530 --> 00:02:47,240
Let's go then.

51
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:47,960
We can eat and talk

52
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:49,370
in that Chinese restaurant.

53
00:02:49,370 --> 00:02:50,500
Are you that hungry?

54
00:02:50,650 --> 00:02:51,800
Isn't he a fellow countryman?

55
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:53,150
Seriously, dining with a random guy?

56
00:02:53,150 --> 00:02:53,900
If you're going out to eat,

57
00:02:53,900 --> 00:02:55,700
shouldn't you run it by me first?

58
00:02:56,410 --> 00:02:56,970
Mr. Du.

59
00:02:58,130 --> 00:02:59,340
Just cut to the chase.

60
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:02,000
Time is money.

61
00:03:03,020 --> 00:03:04,810
Right. I do have something

62
00:03:04,810 --> 00:03:05,940
to discuss with you.

63
00:03:06,430 --> 00:03:08,710
I sell leather shoes,

64
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:10,810
and I'd like to team up with you.

65
00:03:13,910 --> 00:03:16,030
Come on, look at my shoes.

66
00:03:16,810 --> 00:03:18,940
See if they can be added to your outfits

67
00:03:19,130 --> 00:03:20,800
and sell more with your help, okay?

68
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:21,400
This is...

69
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:22,820
mutually beneficial.

70
00:03:23,930 --> 00:03:24,590
Take a look.

71
00:03:27,470 --> 00:03:28,530
The shoes are nice.

72
00:03:33,530 --> 00:03:34,370
Sorry,

73
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:36,030
we don't sell leather shoes.

74
00:03:36,030 --> 00:03:36,890
Take them back.

75
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:42,930
What do you mean?

76
00:03:43,860 --> 00:03:44,920
We're all Chinese.

77
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:46,880
Why not make money together?

78
00:03:47,579 --> 00:03:50,110
It's not a decent move
to keep all the benefits

79
00:03:50,690 --> 00:03:51,579
to yourselves.

80
00:03:53,020 --> 00:03:53,710
Du,

81
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:55,630
it's rude of you to say that.

82
00:03:55,630 --> 00:03:56,500
How am I rude?

83
00:03:57,030 --> 00:03:57,740
We sell outfits,

84
00:03:57,740 --> 00:03:58,800
not leather shoes.

85
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:00,190
We're not standing in your way.

86
00:04:00,190 --> 00:04:00,680
No,

87
00:04:00,810 --> 00:04:02,810
-my only purpose here is...
-Mr. Du.

88
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:05,060
These leather shoes of yours

89
00:04:05,060 --> 00:04:07,150
are called flashy junk
in where we're from.

90
00:04:07,150 --> 00:04:08,800
They can only last for a short time.

91
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:09,970
We refuse to sell anything

92
00:04:09,970 --> 00:04:10,830
of low quality.

93
00:04:13,710 --> 00:04:14,240
Indeed.

94
00:04:15,410 --> 00:04:17,010
But quality doesn't matter,

95
00:04:17,220 --> 00:04:18,720
as long as the goods can sell.

96
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:19,329
Right?

97
00:04:20,070 --> 00:04:21,800
It's not like we're tricking Chinese.

98
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,650
Why are you being so serious?

99
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:25,000
Let's just make money.

100
00:04:25,430 --> 00:04:27,040
You are truly a disgrace to us Chinese.

101
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:27,430
I...

102
00:04:27,870 --> 00:04:29,310
Very well said.

103
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:31,380
Alright. Liangliang,

104
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:32,560
see the guest out.

105
00:04:33,130 --> 00:04:33,620
Mr. Du.

106
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:34,159
No...

107
00:04:34,950 --> 00:04:38,060
See you later.

108
00:04:38,330 --> 00:04:38,990
No, wait...

109
00:04:41,130 --> 00:04:42,659
What kind of person is that?

110
00:04:42,810 --> 00:04:44,690
He looks self-righteous
though he sells fakes.

111
00:04:44,690 --> 00:04:45,420
Don't be mad.

112
00:04:45,830 --> 00:04:46,860
His goods are of poor quality.

113
00:04:46,860 --> 00:04:48,430
There won't be return customers.

114
00:04:48,430 --> 00:04:49,250
Over time,

115
00:04:49,330 --> 00:04:50,220
the reputation of Chinese merchants

116
00:04:50,220 --> 00:04:51,870
in overseas markets will be damaged.

117
00:04:51,870 --> 00:04:52,560
There is so much

118
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:53,690
good stuff in China.

119
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:54,810
Why does he have to sell fakes?

120
00:04:54,810 --> 00:04:55,420
Listen,

121
00:04:55,510 --> 00:04:56,390
these days,

122
00:04:56,420 --> 00:04:57,720
Chinese merchandise is selling better

123
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:58,430
and better in Russia.

124
00:04:58,430 --> 00:04:59,950
The market is getting bigger and bigger.

125
00:04:59,950 --> 00:05:00,610
Meanwhile,

126
00:05:00,630 --> 00:05:02,100
all kinds of shady people are showing up.

127
00:05:02,100 --> 00:05:03,450
There are many, many unscrupulous traders.

128
00:05:03,450 --> 00:05:03,980
Previously,

129
00:05:03,980 --> 00:05:05,310
a batch of down jackets came from China.

130
00:05:05,310 --> 00:05:07,250
Yet there aren't many feathers in them.

131
00:05:07,250 --> 00:05:08,190
See, Russians have to endure

132
00:05:08,190 --> 00:05:08,860
cold winters here.

133
00:05:08,860 --> 00:05:09,890
Some kids wore those clothes and said,

134
00:05:09,890 --> 00:05:10,510
"I hate the clothes

135
00:05:10,510 --> 00:05:11,540
sold by Chinese people the most."

136
00:05:11,540 --> 00:05:12,890
That's awful to hear, isn't it?

137
00:05:12,890 --> 00:05:13,770
How embarrassing.

138
00:05:13,770 --> 00:05:14,430
Yes.

139
00:05:15,220 --> 00:05:17,860
When the reputation is gone,
everything is gone.

140
00:05:17,860 --> 00:05:19,000
This must be Sophia, right?

141
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:19,660
Zhuang Zhuang,

142
00:05:19,660 --> 00:05:20,740
let me get the door.

143
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:23,440
Shall we heat up the food?

144
00:05:28,310 --> 00:05:29,180
What are you doing?

145
00:05:29,180 --> 00:05:30,510
What do you mean by this?

146
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:34,310
Who are you?

147
00:05:34,370 --> 00:05:35,890
Don't move! Back off!

148
00:05:36,540 --> 00:05:38,190
Stop there!

149
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:40,740
Let go!

150
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:42,120
Let go!

151
00:05:42,190 --> 00:05:43,330
Let go of him right now!

152
00:05:43,330 --> 00:05:44,060
Let go of him!

153
00:05:44,860 --> 00:05:45,630
Shut up.

154
00:05:49,390 --> 00:05:49,920
Let go.

155
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:52,730
Liangliang, let go.

156
00:05:53,130 --> 00:05:54,100
Liangliang, let go.

157
00:05:54,100 --> 00:05:55,370
Hands off.

158
00:05:59,740 --> 00:06:02,630
Seems like many people are after you.

159
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:05,390
Sophia lent this place to you,

160
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:06,370
didn't she?

161
00:06:06,570 --> 00:06:07,300
Where is she?

162
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:09,810
I meant to talk to her.

163
00:06:12,740 --> 00:06:13,620
Mr. Sergey,

164
00:06:14,370 --> 00:06:15,300
long time no see.

165
00:06:17,890 --> 00:06:18,540
What?

166
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:20,300
You're still in this area?

167
00:06:20,300 --> 00:06:21,400
This is my turf.

168
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:23,570
Where else would I be?

169
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:25,390
As you Chinese always say,

170
00:06:26,100 --> 00:06:28,230
everyone should get a piece of the pie.

171
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:32,010
But you keep making money yourself
in secret.

172
00:06:34,130 --> 00:06:35,530
That's not appropriate.

173
00:06:35,659 --> 00:06:36,430
I heard

174
00:06:36,980 --> 00:06:37,750
your goods

175
00:06:38,070 --> 00:06:39,800
have been selling well lately.

176
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:42,659
You've made a name for yourself
in our market.

177
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:45,970
With all that money you've earned,

178
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:49,360
a small token of appreciation...

179
00:06:49,870 --> 00:06:50,670
is called for.

180
00:06:51,570 --> 00:06:53,230
Isn't it only fitting to do so?

181
00:06:56,620 --> 00:06:57,680
Yes, you're right.

182
00:06:58,810 --> 00:07:00,600
But don't you usually collect fees

183
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:02,010
directly from the stall?

184
00:07:02,860 --> 00:07:03,860
We really didn't see you when we were

185
00:07:03,860 --> 00:07:05,360
doing business here this time.

186
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:07,890
We thought you were off
making a fortune elsewhere.

187
00:07:07,890 --> 00:07:09,690
We're both trying to earn money.

188
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:11,920
you didn't have to bring a gang here.

189
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:12,630
Look,

190
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:14,390
why not just tell us

191
00:07:14,390 --> 00:07:15,990
what we can do to satisfy you?

192
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:18,040
Right.

193
00:07:18,430 --> 00:07:19,510
It's our first time

194
00:07:19,510 --> 00:07:20,710
doing business here.

195
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:21,810
We don't know

196
00:07:21,810 --> 00:07:23,180
much about your rules.

197
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:25,600
Pretty smart.

198
00:07:29,370 --> 00:07:32,010
But it's a bit too late, isn't it?

199
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,070
Now, you guys

200
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:37,170
have really livened up the market.

201
00:07:37,330 --> 00:07:38,530
Everyone has seen it.

202
00:07:38,830 --> 00:07:40,430
You've earned a good amount,

203
00:07:40,620 --> 00:07:42,350
yet you've never paid me a dime.

204
00:07:42,890 --> 00:07:45,210
How am I supposed
to manage the market then?

205
00:07:45,210 --> 00:07:46,140
Should I just...

206
00:07:46,630 --> 00:07:48,180
let everyone make money here

207
00:07:48,180 --> 00:07:49,310
and leave without a price?

208
00:07:49,310 --> 00:07:50,540
What are you trying to say?

209
00:07:50,540 --> 00:07:51,920
-Get to point.
-Quiet.

210
00:07:53,950 --> 00:07:57,280
Yes, we've made some money.

211
00:07:59,870 --> 00:08:00,600
I know.

212
00:08:01,070 --> 00:08:02,000
I know the rules.

213
00:08:02,810 --> 00:08:04,180
How about this?

214
00:08:05,220 --> 00:08:06,550
Harmony brings wealth.

215
00:08:07,300 --> 00:08:08,300
Just name a price.

216
00:08:08,690 --> 00:08:09,250
Okay.

217
00:08:10,920 --> 00:08:13,300
"Harmony brings wealth." That sounds good.

218
00:08:13,300 --> 00:08:15,560
I'd like to sell what you're selling now.

219
00:08:16,570 --> 00:08:17,930
I also want to make big money.

220
00:08:17,930 --> 00:08:19,630
That makes our conversation easier.

221
00:08:19,630 --> 00:08:21,160
Bring your goods over then.

222
00:08:21,190 --> 00:08:22,220
We'll sell them for you.

223
00:08:22,220 --> 00:08:23,330
We'll do all the hard work

224
00:08:23,330 --> 00:08:23,890
free of charge.

225
00:08:23,890 --> 00:08:25,390
All the profits will be yours.

226
00:08:25,390 --> 00:08:26,650
Or you can just join us.

227
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:27,720
Put in an investment,

228
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:29,240
and we'll split the earnings with you.

229
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:29,970
Is that okay?

230
00:08:32,250 --> 00:08:33,850
What if I don't invest at all?

231
00:08:36,460 --> 00:08:37,120
Mr. Sergey,

232
00:08:37,940 --> 00:08:39,940
we have to pay a lot for our supplies.

233
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:41,150
If you are to partner with us,

234
00:08:41,150 --> 00:08:42,480
you have to invest a sum.

235
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:44,230
Or it won't be fair, will it?

236
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:48,030
Who said I wouldn't invest?

237
00:08:48,650 --> 00:08:50,290
The money you've made here

238
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:52,150
is my capital.

239
00:08:53,150 --> 00:08:55,210
Your business is soaring these days.

240
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:56,250
You must've

241
00:08:56,250 --> 00:08:57,780
accumulated much capital.

242
00:08:57,910 --> 00:09:00,030
Plus, I have many sales channels

243
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:02,280
that can help you make big money.

244
00:09:02,770 --> 00:09:04,170
When there's an earning,

245
00:09:05,390 --> 00:09:06,720
I'll probably consider

246
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:08,680
sharing the profits with you

247
00:09:09,010 --> 00:09:11,580
or returning the capital to you.

248
00:09:16,770 --> 00:09:17,430
Mr. Sergey,

249
00:09:18,630 --> 00:09:19,830
to tell you the truth,

250
00:09:21,700 --> 00:09:23,030
our goods have sold out.

251
00:09:25,390 --> 00:09:26,160
Now, if we are

252
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:27,840
to get a new batch,

253
00:09:28,630 --> 00:09:30,630
it'll likely take more than 10 days.

254
00:09:32,390 --> 00:09:33,070
Well,

255
00:09:34,030 --> 00:09:36,160
there is still some time until winter.

256
00:09:36,340 --> 00:09:38,740
I'll give you...15 days.

257
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:40,100
Okay.

258
00:09:41,250 --> 00:09:42,450
Then you must promise

259
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:43,870
not to cause us

260
00:09:43,870 --> 00:09:45,600
any trouble in the next 15 days.

261
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:47,740
I'll make sure you receive a huge return.

262
00:09:47,740 --> 00:09:48,410
After all,

263
00:09:49,530 --> 00:09:50,460
before we came to do business here,

264
00:09:50,460 --> 00:09:51,790
we hadn't informed you.

265
00:09:51,890 --> 00:09:52,950
That was our fault.

266
00:09:54,150 --> 00:09:54,890
Ma Xiaojun.

267
00:09:56,530 --> 00:09:58,790
You really are smart.

268
00:09:59,940 --> 00:10:01,750
But I have to say this again:

269
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:04,740
don't get clever with me.

270
00:10:19,010 --> 00:10:19,600
Hold it.

271
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:29,040
They're gone.

272
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:32,750
If we weren't in Russia

273
00:10:33,860 --> 00:10:35,080
but Beijing,

274
00:10:36,030 --> 00:10:37,630
I would've slapped that guy,

275
00:10:37,870 --> 00:10:39,580
regardless of who he is.

276
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:40,940
Xiaojun,

277
00:10:41,740 --> 00:10:42,550
previously,

278
00:10:42,550 --> 00:10:44,390
Sergey's turf expanded again.

279
00:10:45,090 --> 00:10:46,120
He's been collecting

280
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:48,700
protection fees arbitrarily
in the nearby markets.

281
00:10:48,700 --> 00:10:51,240
He particularly hates
to see foreigners make money.

282
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:52,510
To add to that, you've been faring so well

283
00:10:52,510 --> 00:10:53,670
in your business lately.

284
00:10:53,670 --> 00:10:56,130
I'm sure he won't easily
let you off the hook.

285
00:10:57,150 --> 00:10:58,560
If we partner with him,

286
00:10:58,870 --> 00:10:59,580
he definitely won't

287
00:10:59,580 --> 00:11:00,510
share profits with us.

288
00:11:00,510 --> 00:11:02,170
He's practically robbing us.

289
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:05,080
Can't someone do something
about these people?

290
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:05,940
How about this?

291
00:11:06,510 --> 00:11:07,240
Let's not...

292
00:11:07,390 --> 00:11:09,140
cause trouble for Sophia

293
00:11:09,370 --> 00:11:10,980
or ourselves.

294
00:11:11,010 --> 00:11:12,340
Since you've made Sergey a promise,

295
00:11:12,340 --> 00:11:13,510
we might as well give him money

296
00:11:13,510 --> 00:11:15,110
and retreat back to Beijing.

297
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,570
Composure is a must in doing business.

298
00:11:18,790 --> 00:11:19,990
What's this rush for?

299
00:11:20,770 --> 00:11:21,650
I admit that at first,

300
00:11:21,650 --> 00:11:23,250
I was quite afraid of Sergey.

301
00:11:23,740 --> 00:11:24,700
I feared nothing

302
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:25,720
but that he might

303
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:26,630
take away all the money

304
00:11:26,630 --> 00:11:27,760
you worked hard for.

305
00:11:28,220 --> 00:11:29,080
Think about it.

306
00:11:29,890 --> 00:11:30,650
He has no idea of the amount

307
00:11:30,650 --> 00:11:31,670
of the capital in our hands.

308
00:11:31,670 --> 00:11:32,370
Neither is he aware

309
00:11:32,370 --> 00:11:33,370
of where we get our suppliers

310
00:11:33,370 --> 00:11:34,530
or how many goods we'll buy.

311
00:11:34,530 --> 00:11:36,130
He doesn't need to know that.

312
00:11:36,130 --> 00:11:37,580
He already considers your money and goods

313
00:11:37,580 --> 00:11:39,620
to be his
whether you continue the business or not.

314
00:11:39,620 --> 00:11:41,080
Plus, you've already made him a promise.

315
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:42,770
What's the point of talking tough here?

316
00:11:42,770 --> 00:11:43,240
Come on.

317
00:11:43,250 --> 00:11:45,110
Don't chime in when I'm speaking.

318
00:11:45,150 --> 00:11:46,080
Come here, come.

319
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:46,850
Take my seat.

320
00:11:47,980 --> 00:11:48,580
Be seated.

321
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:55,220
Here's my thought on this matter.

322
00:11:55,410 --> 00:11:56,770
We should continue to pick up goods

323
00:11:56,770 --> 00:11:57,770
from Vladivostok

324
00:11:58,010 --> 00:11:59,670
and keep on with our business.

325
00:12:00,150 --> 00:12:01,360
No risk, no reward.

326
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:02,360
Jun,

327
00:12:03,030 --> 00:12:03,720
I remember

328
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:06,580
you saying that shipment
from Vladivostok is huge.

329
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:09,630
Are you planning to save a batch

330
00:12:09,630 --> 00:12:10,840
for us to sell on our own?

331
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:11,370
Exactly!

332
00:12:12,820 --> 00:12:13,870
You all know how beautiful

333
00:12:13,870 --> 00:12:14,550
and kind Sophia is.

334
00:12:14,550 --> 00:12:15,290
But what you don't know

335
00:12:15,290 --> 00:12:16,130
is that she is actually

336
00:12:16,130 --> 00:12:17,390
a great businesswoman

337
00:12:17,670 --> 00:12:19,480
with a good reputation and credibility.

338
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:21,610
Sophia, I'd like to ask you for a favor.

339
00:12:22,100 --> 00:12:23,360
Could you introduce us

340
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:25,000
to the merchants you know who are nice

341
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,130
and capable of handling a massive deal

342
00:12:26,130 --> 00:12:26,960
like this, so we can

343
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:28,220
talk to them ourselves?

344
00:12:28,220 --> 00:12:29,820
The more familiar they're with you,
the better.

345
00:12:29,820 --> 00:12:31,840
They have to be so close to you
that Sergey doesn't even

346
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:32,790
know of or has met them,

347
00:12:32,790 --> 00:12:35,450
to the extent where they'd agree
to talk at home.

348
00:12:36,550 --> 00:12:38,390
Your goods are of high quality,

349
00:12:39,030 --> 00:12:40,830
and you've risen to fame lately.

350
00:12:41,740 --> 00:12:43,940
It shouldn't be hard to do what you said.

351
00:12:43,960 --> 00:12:44,530
Look,

352
00:12:44,910 --> 00:12:46,970
Sophia has done us a huge favor again.

353
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:47,940
How about this?

354
00:12:47,940 --> 00:12:49,400
When we go back to Beijing,

355
00:12:50,150 --> 00:12:51,480
we'll leave Jun with you

356
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:53,620
as a gift from us. Okay?

357
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:55,480
You... I...

358
00:12:55,620 --> 00:12:57,000
See, you two are really...

359
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:58,600
No, we're just good friends.

360
00:12:58,630 --> 00:13:01,130
-It's only right to help each other.
-Yes, we’re good friends.

361
00:13:01,130 --> 00:13:02,590
You seem quite happy to me.

362
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:04,020
However...

363
00:13:05,940 --> 00:13:07,940
be clear about the ugly truth first.

364
00:13:08,100 --> 00:13:09,560
There are bound to be risks

365
00:13:10,250 --> 00:13:12,170
in doing business.

366
00:13:13,130 --> 00:13:14,220
If in the end,

367
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:15,770
we lose everything, you...

368
00:13:16,620 --> 00:13:17,650
Jun, stop it.

369
00:13:17,980 --> 00:13:19,370
We'll take it as a life experience then.

370
00:13:19,370 --> 00:13:20,000
Yes.

371
00:13:20,250 --> 00:13:20,980
Bumps are inevitable

372
00:13:20,980 --> 00:13:22,500
along the road of business.

373
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:25,160
We're good friends,
and we're in this together.

374
00:13:25,220 --> 00:13:26,080
Let's go for it!

375
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:29,730
What you said has really...

376
00:13:30,410 --> 00:13:31,720
warmed my heart.

377
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:34,370
Let's go for it then!

378
00:13:34,650 --> 00:13:35,710
Here is my idea.

379
00:13:35,890 --> 00:13:37,250
Tomorrow, you'll go to Vladivostok

380
00:13:37,250 --> 00:13:38,320
to pick up that large shipment.

381
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:39,500
Then, have it

382
00:13:39,670 --> 00:13:40,490
covertly

383
00:13:40,630 --> 00:13:41,840
delivered here in batches.

384
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:42,890
You can go back to Beijing afterwards

385
00:13:42,890 --> 00:13:43,870
and wait to hear from us.

386
00:13:43,870 --> 00:13:44,620
As for us, we...

387
00:13:44,620 --> 00:13:45,250
No, wait, Jun.

388
00:13:45,250 --> 00:13:46,220
How can you assign

389
00:13:46,220 --> 00:13:47,010
such a big task to me?

390
00:13:47,010 --> 00:13:48,200
You think I'm silly or what?

391
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:49,460
Sergey is a terrible menace.

392
00:13:49,460 --> 00:13:50,720
Won't it make me a deserter

393
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:52,030
before battle if I leave?

394
00:13:52,030 --> 00:13:52,910
I must stay here

395
00:13:52,940 --> 00:13:53,780
by your side.

396
00:13:53,890 --> 00:13:55,270
Didn't you say you'd listen to me?

397
00:13:55,270 --> 00:13:56,700
Can I pick up the goods myself?

398
00:13:56,700 --> 00:13:58,150
I have to stay here for negotiations,
don't I?

399
00:13:58,150 --> 00:13:58,790
Besides,

400
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:01,170
I must protect Sophia.

401
00:14:01,220 --> 00:14:03,510
Can we have Zhuang Zhuang
take on the task?

402
00:14:03,510 --> 00:14:04,720
Shengli will definitely disagree, right?

403
00:14:04,720 --> 00:14:05,250
If we let Shengli do it,

404
00:14:05,250 --> 00:14:06,050
Zhuang Zhuang won't agree with it.

405
00:14:06,050 --> 00:14:06,890
Should we let them both go back?

406
00:14:06,890 --> 00:14:08,010
Yes, that's right.

407
00:14:08,010 --> 00:14:08,980
I'll stick with you.

408
00:14:08,980 --> 00:14:09,710
How about...

409
00:14:09,770 --> 00:14:10,920
we hold a vote then?

410
00:14:11,100 --> 00:14:12,620
Raise your hand if you agree
that Zhuang Zhuang and Shengli

411
00:14:12,620 --> 00:14:13,750
should go together.

412
00:14:14,170 --> 00:14:16,230
Raise your hand
if you think Liangliang should go.

413
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:17,150
Alright, it's settled.

414
00:14:17,150 --> 00:14:18,360
It's time I talked about the next steps.

415
00:14:18,360 --> 00:14:18,670
Sit.

416
00:14:21,030 --> 00:14:22,120
Coming!

417
00:14:25,410 --> 00:14:27,450
Long time no see.

418
00:14:27,940 --> 00:14:30,010
Hello, long time no see.

419
00:14:30,050 --> 00:14:31,850
Today has been a really long day.

420
00:14:44,370 --> 00:14:45,410
Okay. Thank you.

421
00:15:02,170 --> 00:15:03,030
Please come in.

422
00:15:04,270 --> 00:15:04,940
Hello!

423
00:15:05,500 --> 00:15:06,050
Hello.

424
00:15:06,240 --> 00:15:07,770
Take a seat. Nice to meet you.

425
00:15:07,770 --> 00:15:09,000
I'm Ma Xiaojun, also known as Lucky Ma.

426
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:09,820
That is Ma Xiaojun.

427
00:15:09,820 --> 00:15:10,320
Hello.

428
00:15:10,790 --> 00:15:11,320
Hello.

429
00:15:13,790 --> 00:15:15,410
These two leather jackets

430
00:15:15,410 --> 00:15:16,880
are our best sellers recently.

431
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:18,080
Top sellers, indeed.

432
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:33,870
[No standing under suspended loads]

433
00:15:42,290 --> 00:15:43,360
Admiring your looks again, huh?

434
00:15:43,360 --> 00:15:44,120
What did you buy?

435
00:15:44,120 --> 00:15:44,890
Check it out.

436
00:15:46,670 --> 00:15:47,750
What are we having for dinner?

437
00:15:47,750 --> 00:15:48,460
Borscht?

438
00:15:48,670 --> 00:15:49,840
Sure. Sounds great!

439
00:15:49,950 --> 00:15:51,030
I'll go find a restaurant for you then.

440
00:15:51,030 --> 00:15:51,410
Okay.

441
00:17:23,089 --> 00:17:24,310
If you don't have better things to do,

442
00:17:24,310 --> 00:17:25,810
go out for a smoke.

443
00:17:27,700 --> 00:17:29,310
Boss, I've got some news.

444
00:17:29,310 --> 00:17:30,960
We found the money.

445
00:17:30,960 --> 00:17:32,350
They hid it somewhere.

446
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:33,900
These people enjoy nothing

447
00:17:33,900 --> 00:17:35,230
but being smarty pants.

448
00:17:36,250 --> 00:17:38,030
Did you catch a glimpse of the amount?

449
00:17:38,030 --> 00:17:39,560
At least tens of thousands.

450
00:17:40,590 --> 00:17:41,350
Keep a close eye on them.

451
00:17:41,350 --> 00:17:43,940
We'll take them all down
once they get the final payment.

452
00:17:43,940 --> 00:17:46,050
Now that the stash place is confirmed,

453
00:17:46,050 --> 00:17:47,590
stop tailing them in the next few days.

454
00:17:47,590 --> 00:17:48,640
Yes, boss.

455
00:17:59,530 --> 00:17:59,990
Here...

456
00:18:00,010 --> 00:18:01,270
What are you two doing?

457
00:18:02,090 --> 00:18:03,510
Zhuang Zhuang is writing a song.

458
00:18:03,510 --> 00:18:04,840
It's very beautiful.

459
00:18:05,030 --> 00:18:05,790
Not at all.

460
00:18:06,070 --> 00:18:07,090
Mr. Zheng told me to compose

461
00:18:07,090 --> 00:18:08,030
a new song, didn't he?

462
00:18:08,030 --> 00:18:09,050
I just got started and asked

463
00:18:09,050 --> 00:18:11,110
Sophia to play accompaniment for me.

464
00:18:12,380 --> 00:18:13,380
Impressive.

465
00:18:13,420 --> 00:18:14,400
You're still carrying on

466
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:15,570
with your music stuff on this trip.

467
00:18:15,570 --> 00:18:16,530
I just wrote a rough draft

468
00:18:16,530 --> 00:18:17,730
based on my feelings.

469
00:18:17,750 --> 00:18:19,160
When we're back,
I still need to have it revised

470
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:19,890
by Mr. Zheng.

471
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:20,730
Alright.

472
00:18:21,530 --> 00:18:22,790
Let me be the audience.

473
00:18:24,380 --> 00:18:24,850
Okay.

474
00:18:25,220 --> 00:18:26,140
Shall we start over

475
00:18:26,140 --> 00:18:27,350
using the melody

476
00:18:27,550 --> 00:18:28,350
we just played?

477
00:18:28,350 --> 00:18:28,770
Sure.

478
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:33,030
One, two, three, four.

479
00:18:52,960 --> 00:18:55,490
You should write this down.
It sounds lovely.

480
00:19:10,750 --> 00:19:11,640
It's really nice.

481
00:19:11,640 --> 00:19:12,900
The song sounds great.

482
00:19:13,850 --> 00:19:14,960
Thank you, Sophia.

483
00:19:15,310 --> 00:19:16,330
Such a beautiful song.

484
00:19:16,330 --> 00:19:17,530
The accompaniment was beautiful too.

485
00:19:17,530 --> 00:19:19,130
Xiaojun, did it go smoothly?

486
00:19:19,290 --> 00:19:19,830
Yes.

487
00:19:20,740 --> 00:19:22,090
Where did you guys go today?

488
00:19:22,090 --> 00:19:23,630
We were off to hide money.

489
00:19:23,900 --> 00:19:24,740
Hide money?

490
00:19:25,770 --> 00:19:26,680
Sophia has introduced

491
00:19:26,680 --> 00:19:27,880
so many clients to us.

492
00:19:28,090 --> 00:19:28,680
Recently,

493
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:29,880
we've received a lot of deposits.

494
00:19:29,880 --> 00:19:32,180
There'll be large final payments
when the goods arrive.

495
00:19:32,180 --> 00:19:34,210
So, we stashed the money

496
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:35,850
in the lockers in batches.

497
00:19:35,850 --> 00:19:37,180
And those people
really fell for our trick.

498
00:19:37,180 --> 00:19:38,180
Sergey must think

499
00:19:38,180 --> 00:19:39,000
everything's under his control.

500
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:40,220
But he could never imagine

501
00:19:40,220 --> 00:19:42,750
that we actually swapped the money
in the end.

502
00:19:42,830 --> 00:19:43,960
Shengli is so smart.

503
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,800
This is an absolutely brilliant

504
00:19:45,940 --> 00:19:46,790
idea of his.

505
00:19:48,510 --> 00:19:49,880
When the last batch of goods arrives,

506
00:19:49,880 --> 00:19:51,940
it'll be time to confront Mr. Sergey.

507
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:55,010
Xiaojun has been clamoring
for mutton hot pot

508
00:19:55,010 --> 00:19:56,400
since yesterday.

509
00:19:56,830 --> 00:19:57,700
What is this?

510
00:19:57,700 --> 00:19:59,360
Are we cooking meat with this?

511
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:00,570
Aren't you ignorant, goof?

512
00:20:00,570 --> 00:20:01,510
This is a samovar.

513
00:20:01,510 --> 00:20:02,420
For making tea?

514
00:20:02,530 --> 00:20:03,010
Yes.

515
00:20:03,420 --> 00:20:05,180
The copper pot Xiaojun brought me

516
00:20:05,180 --> 00:20:06,640
was taken by my friend.

517
00:20:06,770 --> 00:20:08,050
This looks exquisite.

518
00:20:08,160 --> 00:20:08,900
Yes.

519
00:20:09,550 --> 00:20:11,480
How about I bring you one
when I deliver goods

520
00:20:11,480 --> 00:20:12,250
to Beijing?

521
00:20:12,510 --> 00:20:13,050
Great.

522
00:20:13,420 --> 00:20:15,420
Then I'll also send you a copper pot
when I get back.

523
00:20:15,420 --> 00:20:15,880
Okay.

524
00:20:16,230 --> 00:20:17,400
Although this is a samovar,

525
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:18,220
it actually has

526
00:20:18,220 --> 00:20:19,750
the same usage as a copper pot.

527
00:20:19,750 --> 00:20:20,940
Take out that bottle of Erguotou then.

528
00:20:20,940 --> 00:20:21,880
Why not have a few drinks tonight?

529
00:20:21,880 --> 00:20:22,420
Sure.

530
00:20:22,750 --> 00:20:25,090
But I must roll up the carpet first.

531
00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:26,530
No, I won't barf.

532
00:20:26,530 --> 00:20:28,030
Erguotou agrees well with me.

533
00:20:28,030 --> 00:20:29,200
Right? I've had it before with Shengli.

534
00:20:29,200 --> 00:20:29,960
I can manage.

535
00:20:29,980 --> 00:20:31,440
Okay, I'll go find it then.

536
00:20:32,140 --> 00:20:33,990
And I'll go help her with it.

537
00:20:34,720 --> 00:20:35,570
Didn't I bring

538
00:20:35,570 --> 00:20:37,220
that bottle of Erguoto to you

539
00:20:37,290 --> 00:20:38,770
along with that pile of tea leaves?

540
00:20:38,770 --> 00:20:40,900
Such a good life they're having here.

541
00:20:51,330 --> 00:20:52,460
Good take. We got it!

542
00:20:52,590 --> 00:20:54,140
Let's congratulate Ms. Shen Ranran

543
00:20:54,140 --> 00:20:55,400
on wrapping up the filming!

544
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:57,070
-Bravo!
-Bravo!

545
00:20:58,330 --> 00:20:59,130
Thank you all.

546
00:20:59,880 --> 00:21:00,460
Thanks.

547
00:21:02,980 --> 00:21:04,040
Congratulations.

548
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:04,920
Good work.

549
00:21:04,920 --> 00:21:05,780
Thank you, sir.

550
00:21:05,960 --> 00:21:06,960
Sure. We must work together again

551
00:21:06,960 --> 00:21:07,940
if there's a chance. Alright?

552
00:21:07,940 --> 00:21:08,660
Definitely.

553
00:21:08,660 --> 00:21:10,880
-Everyone, good work!
-Thanks for the hard work, everyone!

554
00:21:10,880 --> 00:21:11,420
-Bravo!
-Bravo!

555
00:21:11,420 --> 00:21:13,080
Your performance was spot on.

556
00:21:15,530 --> 00:21:16,250
Ranran,

557
00:21:16,770 --> 00:21:18,630
I have a piece of good news for you.

558
00:21:20,440 --> 00:21:22,170
The crew just called and told me

559
00:21:22,610 --> 00:21:24,400
how wonderful your acting was,

560
00:21:24,850 --> 00:21:27,610
and that you're a nice
and professional actress.

561
00:21:28,530 --> 00:21:29,990
That gave me so much pride,

562
00:21:30,090 --> 00:21:30,620
for real.

563
00:21:31,890 --> 00:21:32,750
Do you remember?

564
00:21:32,750 --> 00:21:33,880
You told me before

565
00:21:34,290 --> 00:21:34,960
that you hoped

566
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:36,010
the crew would thank me

567
00:21:36,010 --> 00:21:37,180
for recommending

568
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:38,510
a good actress to them.

569
00:21:39,250 --> 00:21:40,450
Now, it has come true.

570
00:21:44,160 --> 00:21:47,020
Making a romantic gesture
right after your return?

571
00:21:47,250 --> 00:21:49,850
Waiting for Ranran again,
aren't you, Mr. Tao?

572
00:21:50,980 --> 00:21:51,700
Yes, I am.

573
00:21:55,740 --> 00:21:56,720
Listen,

574
00:21:56,750 --> 00:21:57,510
Ranran said

575
00:21:57,570 --> 00:21:59,250
she would come back today,
but she didn't give

576
